  "prompt": "Why won't IFTTT link to my tumblr account?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why IFTTT might not link to your Tumblr account. Here are some common issues and troubleshooting steps:\n\n1. **Authorization Issues**: Ensure that you have properly authorized IFTTT to access your Tumblr account. Sometimes, authorization can fail due to incorrect credentials or missed steps.\n\n2. **Account Settings**: Verify your Tumblr account settings to make sure there are no restrictions or security settings that might prevent external apps from linking.\n\n3. **Applet Configuration**: Double-check the configuration of the specific applet you are trying to use. Ensure that all settings are correctly configured and that you have selected the correct Tumblr blog if you have multiple blogs.\n\n4. **Platform Rules & Limits**: Tumblr might have its own rules or limits regarding third-party applications. Make sure your Tumblr account complies with these rules.\n\n5. **Browser Issues**: Sometimes, browser caches or extensions can interfere. Try clearing your browser cache or using a different browser.\n\n6. **Connectivity Problems**: There might be temporary server issues either on IFTTT's end or Tumblr's end. Wait for a while and try again later.\n\n7. **Change in API or Services**: Tumblr or IFTTT may have updated their APIs or service offerings, causing temporary or permanent disconnections. Check for any announcements or updates from either platform.\n\n8. **Contact Support**: If none of the above solutions work, it may be best to contact IFTTT support or Tumblr support for further assistance. They can provide specific insights into why the connection might be failing.\n\nBy going through each of these steps, you should be able to identify and possibly resolve the issue preventing IFTTT from linking to your Tumblr account.",
